6. Presets
Card Navigator now supports presets, allowing users to save and switch between different configurations quickly. This feature enhances workflow flexibility by adjusting how notes are displayed and interacted with.
	•	Create Custom Presets: Save the current Card Navigator settings as a named preset for future use.
	•	Global Presets: Set a default preset that applies to all folders (unless overridden by folder-specific settings).
	•	Folder-Specific Presets: Assign different presets to specific folders to customize views based on the folder structure.
	•	Auto-Apply Presets: Automatically switch to the appropriate preset when navigating between folders.
	•	Import/Export Presets: Save presets to a file and share or back them up.
	•	Preset Management: Edit, duplicate, or delete existing presets directly from the settings panel.

How to Use Presets:
	•	Creating a Preset:
	1.	Navigate to the Card Navigator Settings.
	2.	Configure the desired settings.
	3.	Click the ”+” button in the Preset Management section.
	4.	Name the preset and optionally add a description.
	•	Applying a Preset:
	•	Global Preset: Toggle a preset as the default for all folders.
	•	Folder-Specific Preset: Assign a preset to a folder in the Folder Presets section.
	•	Auto-Applying Presets:
	•	Enable “Auto-Apply Presets” in the settings.
	•	Card Navigator will automatically switch to the appropriate preset when changing folders.
	•	Importing/Exporting Presets:
	•	Use the Import/Export buttons in the Preset Management section.
	•	Exported presets are saved as JSON files for easy sharing or backup.

By using presets, users can fine-tune Card Navigator’s behavior based on different note structures or workflows, enhancing productivity and note management experience.

